## Trap-Setting Questions

**Questions that expose their weaknesses and highlight our strengths:**

### Setup & Implementation
- "How long can your team wait for IT to configure a new tool - days or weeks?"
- "When you need to onboard a new hire, can they start immediately or wait for IT to provision access?"
- "What happens when your team needs to get started but IT is backlogged for 3 weeks?"

### Scope & Tool Sprawl
- "Beyond wikis, what else does your team need - tasks, docs, databases?"
- "How many tools would you eliminate if you could handle all team content in one place?"
- "When you're looking for a document, how many tools do you have to search?"

### Adoption & Usage
- "What percentage of your team actually uses your current wiki tool daily?"
- "How often do team members ask 'where's that doc?' in Slack?"
- "If setup took 2 hours instead of 2 weeks, would that change your timeline?"

### Cost & ROI
- "Beyond the software cost, what's the IT setup and ongoing admin time?"
- "How much are you paying per user for tools you could consolidate?"
- "If your team could save 10 hours per week on doc search, what's that worth?"

